MALACAÑANG RESIDENCE OF THE PRESIDENT OF THE PHILIPPINES MANILA

PROCLAMATION NO. 361

RESERVING FOR SCHOOL SITE PURPOSES CERTAIN PARCELS OF THE PRIVATE DOMAIN OF THE GOVERNMENT, SITUATED IN THE CITY OF LEGASPI.

Upon the recommendation of the Secretary of General Services, and pursuant to the provisions of Section 64 (e) of the Revised Administrative Code, in relation to Section I of Republic Act No. 477, I, DIOSDADO MACAPAGAL, President of the Philippines, hereby withdraw from sale or settlement and reserve for school site purposes, under the administration of the Bureau of Public Schools, subject to private rights, if any there be, certain parcels of the private domain of the government situated in the City of Legaspi, and more particularly described as follows:

Lot 9707 Legaspi Cadastre Teodosa Reina

“A parcel of land (lot 9707 of the Cadastral Survey of Legaspi, G.L.R.O. Cad. Record No.    ), situated in the Municipality of Legaspi, Province of Albay. Bounded on the N.W., along lines 1-2 and 2-5, by Lot 9702, Legaspi Cadastre; along lines 5-7, by Lot 1023, Legaspi Cadastre; along line 7-8 by Lot 1024, Legaspi Cadastre; along lines 8-10 by Lot 1025, Legaspi Cadastre; along line 10-11, by Road; along lines 11-13, by Lot 9706, Legaspi Cadastre; along lines 13-15, by Lot 9717, Legaspi Cadastre; and along . lines 15-16 and 16-1, by Lot 9702, Legaspi Cadastre, Beginning at a point marked “1” on plan, being N. 42 deg. 04′ E., 43 8.87 m. from B.L.L.M. 6, Legaspi Cadastre;

