Lot 1025 Legaspi Cadastre

“A parcel of land (lot 1025 of the Cadastral Survey of Legaspi, G.L.R.O. Cadastral Record No.      ), situated in the Municipality of Legaspi, Province of Albay. Bounded on the N.E., along line 1-2 by the Road; along lines 2-4 by Lot 9707, Legaspi Cadastre, and along line 4-1 by Lot 1024, Legaspi Cadastre. Beginning at a point marked “1” on plan, being I. 37 deg. 22′ E., 668.28 m., from B.L.L.M. 6, Legaspi Cadastre;

beginning containing an area of FOUR HUNDRED AND TWENTY NINE (429) SQUARE METERS. All points referred to are indicated on the plan and are marked on the ground by Old Corners; bearings true; date of the cadastral survey, Dec. 1913-March, 1915.”

IN WITNESS WHEREOF, I have hereunto set my hand and caused the seal of the Republic of the Philippines to be affixed.

Done in the City of Manila, this 22nd day of February, in the year of Our Lord, nineteen hundred and sixty-five.

(SGD.) DIOSDADO MACAPAGAL President of the Philippines

By the President:

(SGD.) RAMON A. DIAZ Executive Secretary

